article.description: T.J. Cromer scored 20, including the winning 3-pointer with eight seconds left, and Ge'Lawn Guyn had a career-high 28 points to lead East Tennessee State to an 86-83 win over North Carolina-Green
article.headline: Cromer, Guyn lead ETSU to 86-83 win over UNCG
article.linkText: Cromer, Guyn lead ETSU to 86-83 win over UNCG
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. -- T.J. Cromer scored 20, including the winning 3-pointer with eight seconds left, and Ge'Lawn Guyn had a career-high 28 points to lead East Tennessee State to an 86-83 win over North Carolina-Greensboro on Saturday. Kayel Locke scored 10 straight points for UNCG, the last two of which put the Spartans up 83-80 with 1:37 left. Guyn hit a 3, his sixth of the game, to tie it 27 seconds later. The Buccaneers (9-6, 2-0 Southern Conference) forced a shot-clock violation against UNCG with 36.9 seconds left and Cromer's 3-pointer from the right wing, with the shot clock dwindling, made it 86-83. UNCG's Diante Baldwin missed a potential tying 3 as time expired. The game featured 11 ties and 11 lead changes. Guyn tied a career-high by making 6 of ETSU's school-record 15 3-pointers. Lester Wilson hit 5 3s and scored a season-high 17. Francis Alonso led UNCG (5-11, 1-2) with 21 points. Locke and R.J. White scored 19 apiece.
